 then landed in a designated target zone."SOURCES: CNN, WeChat press release, South China Morning Post, Defence Blog, Asia Times, Xinhua Nethttps://edition.cnn.com/2018/08/07/china/china-hypersonic-aircraft-intl/index.html?no-st=1533692596https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s?subscene=23&__biz=MzI3MDA2NDI2MQ==&mid=2650740091&idx=1&sn=8c2545c20c672d7f52d97fd560abe48c&chksm=f2dd7a91c5aaf38700ba3d259a68661b738e8303f0e4f36b6bee01f770c7e95ceb31ff1b050e&scene=7#rdhttps://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy-defence/article/2158524/chinas-hypersonic-aircraft-starry-sky-2-could-be-used#commentshttps://defence-blog.com/aviation/china-successfully-test-fire-hypersonic-aircraft.htmlhttp://www.atimes.com/article/china-tests-its-hypersonic-wave-rider-aircraft/http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/2018-08/06/c_137370948.htm***]]></description>
