      <title>Woman who fell off cruise ship rescued after floating for 10 hours</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANA British woman on a cruise ship in the Adriatic Sea fell into the water approximately 60 miles off the coast of Croatia and reportedly spent 10 hours treading water before being rescued. The 46-year-old, who some local media identified as Kay Longstaff, said, "I fell off the back of the Norwegian Star and I was in the water for 10 hours, so these wonderful guys rescued me," in an interview with Croatia's state television network HRT. According to the Washington Post, she declined to tell reporters how she fell off the cruise ship. The cruise company is expected to examine closed-circuit camera footage in order to determine the events leading up to the incident. The company said the woman went overboard as the ship was headed to Venice. The ship was stopped and a search mounted after crew realized someone had fallen overboard. Croatian navy and coast guard were also alerted. The navy used a PC-9 aircraft and a patrol boat. Kay was spotted around 9:40 p.m. in the sea and rescued five minutes later.  She was taken to a hospital in Pula, Croatia and is in stable condition.According to the Guardian, the incident is under investigation and the British embassy in Croatia has been informed. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Norwegian Star traveling to Venice2. Kay treading water for 10 hours3. Norwegian Star, Croatian navy and coast guard searching for Kay4. Kay being rescued from waterVOICEOVER (in English): "A British woman on a cruise ship in the Adriatic Sea fell into the water approximately 60 miles off the coast of Croatia as the ship was on its way to Venice and was rescued after almost half a day at sea." "The 46-year-old, who identified herself as Kay to local media, said she fell off the back of the Norwegian Star and then managed to stay afloat for 10 hours."  "After crew realized someone had fallen overboard, the ship was stopped and a search mounted. Croatian navy and coast guard were also alerted. The navy used a PC-9 aircraft and a patrol boat in the search."  "Kay was spotted around 9:40 p.m. in the sea and rescued five minutes later. She was taken to a hospital in Pula, Croatia and is in stable condition."SOURCES: Washington Post, Guardianhttps://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2018/08/19/woman-says-she-fell-off-cruise-ship-spent-hours-adriatic-sea-before-she-was-rescued/?utm_term=.6361b36ebc32https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/aug/19/british-woman-rescued-10-hours-adriatic-sea-cruise-ship-fall***]]></description>
