      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANThe U.S. military is exploring how to take its operations into space.According to a U.S. Department of Defence document, military officials are exploring four components for a proposed Space Force. One of these is a Space Development Agency for primarily research and development.The next would be a Space Operation Force. According to the DOD, this would "develop, field and integrate space capabilities into multi-domain warfighting".Thirdly the U.S. government would explore a Services and Support component for logistical and administrative purposes. The fourth component the DoD are looking at is a U.S. Space Command to lead conflict operations in space. According to Defense One, the creation of a new military branch would need congressional approval but some of it could be delivered by a restructuring of the DoD.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Depiction of scientists developing new space technology2. Depiction of military officials coordinating space operations3. Depiction of a astronaut servicing a space-based facility4. Depiction of a space command operations centerVOICEOVER (in English): "According to a U.S. Department of Defence document, military officials are exploring four components for a proposed Space Force.""One of these is a Space Development Agency for primarily research and development.""The next would be a Space Operation Force.""According to the DOD, this would "develop, field and integrate space capabilities into multi-domain warfighting"." "Thirdly the U.S. government would explore a Services and Support component for logistical and administrative purposes.""The fourth component the DoD are looking at is a U.S. Space Command to lead conflict operations in space." SOURCES: U.S. Department of Defense, Defense One, National Geographic, Planetary Societyhttps://media.defense.gov/2018/Aug/09/2001952764/-1/-1/1/ORGANIZATIONAL-MANAGEMENT-STRUCTURE-DOD-NATIONAL-SECURITY-SPACE-COMPONENTS.PDFhttps://www.defenseone.com/politics/2018/07/pentagon-create-space-force/150157/https://news.nationalgeographic.com/2018/06/space-force-trump-legal-military-role-satellites-science/http://www.planetary.org/blogs/casey-dreier/2018/0823-space-force-explainer.html***]]></description>
